entation and the realities of race for Asian American college students.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 10. Jan 2022) 0aAsian American college studentsxEthnic identityzIllinoiszChampaign. 0aAsian American college studentsxSocial conditionszIllinoiszChampaign. 0aAsian American college studentszIllinoiszChampaignxEthnic identity. 0aAsian American college studentszIllinoiszChampaignxSocial conditions. 0aStudent movementszIllinoiszChampaignxHistoryy20th century. 0aStudent movementszIllinoiszChampaignxHistoryy21st century. 7aEDUCATION / General.2bisacsh  aAsian, American, model minority, diversity, education, model minority myth, under-representation, black-white, Asian American Studies, race, Asian college students, student services, higher education, cultural values, political passivity.1 aLott, Joy Williamson-.40uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978197882448540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781978824485423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781978824485/original  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK